GROSS DESCRIPTION : A. Received fresh for Tissue Banking labeled with the patient 's name and left lower lobe .
Received is a 200 gram 15.0 x 7.5 x 3.5 cm lobe of lung .
The pleural surface is pink/tan to purple with scant anthracotic marbling .
There is a focal 1.5 x 1.0 cm area of disruption on the pleural surface laterally .
No additional pleural lesions are identified .
The lung is sectioned to have a 1.2 x 1.0 x 0.9 cm central indurated white tumor mass .
The tumor is 2.0 cm from the bronchial margin and between 1.5 and 2.0 cm to the pleura .
A section is sampled for Tissue Banking .
The tumor appears to surround the adjacent vasculature and air ways .
The tumor is centrally located within the lobe .
The remainder of the parenchyma is unremarkable and no additional lesions or dilated airspaces are identified .
